body:
Before, the MLIR code below produced the following Verilog code:
```
hw.module.extern @B() -> (%B_output : i32)

hw.module @A() -> (%A_output : i32) {
    %0 = hw.instance "b1" @B() : () -> (i32)
    hw.output %0 : i32
}
```
```
// external module B

module A(
  output [31:0] A_output);

  wire b1_b_output

  B b1 (        // ../test.mlir:4:10
    .B_output (b1_b_output)
  );

  assign A_output = b1_b_output;
endmodule
```

With this pull request, the above MLIR code becomes:
```
// external module B

module A(
  output [31:0] A_output);

  B b1 (        // ../test.mlir:4:10
    .B_output (A_output)
  );
endmodule
```

The intermediate wire is removed and the output of the instance is directly assigned to the output of the module. This does not apply to instances where the output of an instance is used in multiple places:
```
hw.module.extern @B() -> (%B_output : i32)
hw.module.extern @C(%c_in : i32) -> ()

hw.module @A() -> (%A_output : i32) {
    %0 = hw.instance "b1" @B() : () -> (i32)
    hw.instance "c1" @C(%0) : (i32) -> ()
    hw.output %0 : i32
}
```
```
// external module B

// external module C

module A(
  output [31:0] A_output);

  wire [31:0] b1_B_output;      // ../test.mlir:5:10

  B b1 (        // ../test.mlir:5:10
    .B_output (b1_B_output)
  );
  C c1 (        // ../test.mlir:6:5
    .c_in (b1_B_output) // ../test.mlir:5:10
  );
  assign A_output = b1_B_output;        // ../test.mlir:5:10, :7:5
endmodule
```
